<span id="freeTextContainer9648618516086941620">Like a tight rock-n-roll song or elegantly written piece of computer code, Pepperland reflects its creator as an artist at the top of his game. Wightman captures the essence of the 1970’s with keen-eyed detail and a briskly-paced plot. He combines a touch of magical realism with a dab of bildungsroman and tops it with a thick layer of high-flying suspense. I have never been a male, computer-genius, rising rock star in my early 20’s, but I sure feel like I’ve had that experience after reading thi</span>
  <span id="freeText9648618516086941620" style="display:none">Like a tight rock-n-roll song or elegantly written piece of computer code, Pepperland reflects its creator as an artist at the top of his game. Wightman captures the essence of the 1970’s with keen-eyed detail and a briskly-paced plot. He combines a touch of magical realism with a dab of bildungsroman and tops it with a thick layer of high-flying suspense. I have never been a male, computer-genius, rising rock star in my early 20’s, but I sure feel like I’ve had that experience after reading this book. What a fun ride.</span>
